name: Petroglyphs n.6
description:
Purchase this wonderful drawing on paper. 

Technique: Watercolor
Size: 24 x 32 cm
Year: 2013
Author: Fernando Vélez Castro

This piece is unique, one-of-a-kind artwork, and belongs to the series Petroglyphs. 

Petroglyphs (also called rock engravings) are pictogram and logogram images created by removing part of a rock surface by incising, picking, carving, and abrading (Source: wikipedia)

What I see,what I feel with this series:

"Your hands
everywhere I look
your hands
petrified poems on the 
border...."

name: Verdigris n.8
description:
You shall love this beautiful series of drawings called "Verdigris" 

Technique: Watercolor
Size: 24 x 30 cm
Year: 2011
Author: Fernando Vélez Castro

This gorgeous creation is one-of-a-kind piece, and belongs to the series "Verdigris".

Verdigris is the common name for a green pigment obtained through the application of acetic acid to copper plates[1] or the natural patina formed when copper, brass or bronze is weathered and exposed to air or seawater over a period of time. (Source: Wikipedia)

What I see,what I feel with this series:

"In a minimal forest, in a moss poem, musk in my neck….I sleep in your plant landscape…."
